cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for synthesizing facial images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training a decoder network using a feature vector that is largely invariant to lighting, pose, and facial expression, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves generating facial landmarks and textures, which could be considered a form of artificial intelligence, placing it under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves image warping operations, which could fall under the category of cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper mentions creating a 3-D avatar, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
